 "cells": [
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Project 7 — Local Research Paper Explainer\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Explain Research Papers in Plain English\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Goal:** Parse a research paper, summarize each section, produce a glossary,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"and generate key takeaway cards — all locally.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Stack:** Ollama · LangChain · PyPDF · fpdf2 · Jupyter\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### What You'll Learn\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Section-aware parsing\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Multi-level summarization\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Glossary extraction\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Key takeaway generation\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Prerequisites\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Ollama running with `qwen3:8b` pulled\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# !pip install -q langchain langchain-ollama langchain-core langchain-community fpdf2 pypdf\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Step 1 — Setup and Sample Paper\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"from langchain_ollama import ChatOllama\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from langchain_core.prompts import ChatPromptTemplate\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from langchain_core.output_parsers import StrOutputParser\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import requests\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    r = requests.get(\\\"http://localhost:11434/api/tags\\\", timeout=5)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"Ollama running — {len(r.json().get('models', []))} models\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except: print(\\\"Start Ollama first!\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"llm = ChatOllama(model=\\\"qwen3:8b\\\", temperature=0.2)\"\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sample_paper = {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Attention Is All You Need\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"abstract\\\": \\\"\\\"\\\"The dominant sequence transduction models are based on complex\\n\",\n",
    "    \"recurrent or convolutional neural networks that include an encoder and a decoder.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The best performing models also connect the encoder and decoder through an\\n\",\n",
    "    \"attention mechanism. We propose a new simple network architecture, the Transformer,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"based solely on attention mechanisms, dispensing with recurrence and convolutions\\n\",\n",
    "    \"entirely. Experiments on two machine translation tasks show these models to be\\n\",\n",
    "    \"superior in quality while being more parallelizable and requiring significantly\\n\",\n",
    "    \"less time to train.\\\"\\\"\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"sections\\\": {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"Introduction\\\": \\\"\\\"\\\"Recurrent neural networks, long short-term memory and gated\\n\",\n",
    "    \"recurrent neural networks have been established as state of the art approaches in\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sequence modeling and transduction problems. The Transformer is the first\\n\",\n",
    "    \"transduction model relying entirely on self-attention to compute representations.\\\"\\\"\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"Self-Attention\\\": \\\"\\\"\\\"An attention function maps a query and a set of key-value\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pairs to an output. We call our particular attention Scaled Dot-Product Attention.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Multi-Head Attention allows the model to jointly attend to information from\\n\",\n",
    "    \"different representation subspaces at different positions.\\\"\\\"\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"Architecture\\\": \\\"\\\"\\\"The encoder maps an input sequence to a sequence of continuous\\n\",\n",
    "    \"representations. The decoder generates an output sequence of symbols one at a time.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The Transformer follows this overall architecture using stacked self-attention and\\n\",\n",
    "    \"point-wise, fully connected layers for both encoder and decoder.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    }\\n\",\n",
    "    \"}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Loaded paper: {sample_paper['title']}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Step 2 — Section-by-Section Explanation\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"explain_prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"system\\\", \\\"\\\"\\\"You explain research paper sections in plain English.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Target audience: smart undergraduate who hasn't studied this field.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Use analogies and everyday examples\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Define technical terms when first used\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Keep explanations under 200 words per section\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Highlight the key insight of each section\\\"\\\"\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"human\\\", \\\"\\\"\\\"Paper: {title}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Section: {section_name}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Content: {section_content}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Explain this section in plain English.\\\"\\\"\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"explain_chain = explain_prompt | llm | StrOutputParser()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"# {sample_paper['title']}\\\\n\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"## Abstract (Plain English)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"abstract_explained = explain_chain.invoke({\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"title\\\": sample_paper[\\\"title\\\"],\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"section_name\\\": \\\"Abstract\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"section_content\\\": sample_paper[\\\"abstract\\\"],\\n\",\n",
    "    \"})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(abstract_explained)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for section_name, content in sample_paper[\\\"sections\\\"].items():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"\\\\n## {section_name} (Plain English)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    explanation = explain_chain.invoke({\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"title\\\": sample_paper[\\\"title\\\"],\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"section_name\\\": section_name,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"section_content\\\": content,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    })\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(explanation)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Step 3 — Key Takeaways Extractor\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"from pydantic import BaseModel, Field\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"class PaperTakeaways(BaseModel):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    one_sentence_summary: str\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    key_contribution: str\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    main_technique: str\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    practical_applications: list[str]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    limitations: list[str]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    prerequisites_to_understand: list[str]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"takeaway_llm = llm.with_structured_output(PaperTakeaways)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"full_text = f\\\"Title: {sample_paper['title']}\\\\nAbstract: {sample_paper['abstract']}\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for name, content in sample_paper[\\\"sections\\\"].items():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    full_text += f\\\"\\\\n\\\\n{name}: {content}\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"takeaways = takeaway_llm.invoke(f\\\"Extract key takeaways from this paper:\\\\n\\\\n{full_text}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"One-Sentence Summary: {takeaways.one_sentence_summary}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Key Contribution: {takeaways.key_contribution}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Main Technique: {takeaways.main_technique}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\nApplications:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for a in takeaways.practical_applications:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"  • {a}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\nLimitations:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for l in takeaways.limitations:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"  • {l}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Step 4 — Generate Quiz Questions\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"quiz_prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"system\\\", \\\"Generate 5 quiz questions about this research paper. Include \\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"     \\\"multiple choice (4 options each) and short answer questions. Provide the \\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"     \\\"correct answers.\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"human\\\", \\\"{paper_text}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"quiz_chain = quiz_prompt | llm | StrOutputParser()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"quiz = quiz_chain.invoke({\\\"paper_text\\\": full_text})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Quiz Questions:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(quiz)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## What You Learned\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Section-by-section explanation** with audience-aware prompts\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Structured takeaway extraction** with Pydantic\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Quiz generation** from academic content\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Use a real arXiv paper and run the pipeline\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Add a glossary of technical terms\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Generate multi-level summaries (beginner, expert)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"*Next: **08 — Local Blog-to-Thread Converter***\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
